Euler's Totient Series
\layout Standard

Consider the Maclaurin series
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
M_{\Phi}(x)=(1-\left|x\right|)^{2}\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}x^{n-1}\phi(n)\label{eq:}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi(n)$
\end_inset 

 is Euler's Totient function.
 A graph of this function appears below.
 The limit of the series as 
\begin_inset Formula $x\rightarrow1$
\end_inset 

 appears to be 
\begin_inset Formula \[
M_{\phi}(1)=0.60792710185(1)\]

\end_inset 

where the value in parenthesis is the uncertainty in the last digit.
 Other special values (all of which are easy to calculate) include 
\begin_inset Formula \[
2M_{\phi}(1/2)=2\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\phi(n)/2^{n}=1.7352616039700447...\]

\end_inset 

 
\begin_inset Formula \[
3\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\phi(n)/3^{n}=0.698640937680928825...\]

\end_inset 


\begin_inset Formula \[
4\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\phi(n)/4^{n}=0.425655257611738727...\]

\end_inset 

 
\begin_inset Formula \[
5\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\phi(n)/5^{n}=0.303493769678081032...\]

\end_inset 

 
\begin_inset Formula \[
M_{\phi}(2/3)=0.527545959546096966...\]

\end_inset 

 
\begin_inset Formula \[
M_{\phi}(2/5)=0.363055654428664446...\]

\end_inset 

 It would be interesting to know what the analytic structure of 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{phi}$
\end_inset 

 is.
 
